POD1000000013_S0000070	okay so ah for for our english listeners and for those in the united states northern ireland is obviously unique politically and socially
POD1000000013_S0000071	but i don't think that many of us have a great deal of understanding of how this must have impacted on your work as an ombudsman
POD1000000013_S0000072	could you say a little bit about that
POD1000000013_S0000073	well i think because the first ombudsman's office in northern ireland was created in nineteen sixty-nine so we are we are celebrating our fiftieth anniversary year this year
POD1000000013_S0000074	it was it was created to deal with complaints of discrimination in housing employment and particularly in local government
POD1000000013_S0000075	i think that the genesis the idea for an ombudsman was to bring fairness to the citizen
POD1000000013_S0000076	and i think that's that's really been always a a a a key element of the work of the office
POD1000000013_S0000077	i mean we feel it very very strongly that we are in the justice business that it is about but you know being fair
POD1000000013_S0000078	and not only being fair to complainants or people who feel the public services services have failed them but being fair to to to those that are wrongly criticised or wrongly blamed
POD1000000013_S0000079	because i think an ombudsman the role of an ombudsman is also to provide vindication when things gone right
POD1000000013_S0000080	what about the impact of sectarianism on your work both inside the office and externally as as ombudsman
POD1000000013_S0000081	well we you know i have ah a workforce who believe totally my staff totally believe in fairness and equality
POD1000000013_S0000082	and it doesn't matter who complains to the office that it doesn't matter who complains or what the nature of the complaint is that we're gonna deal with it
POD1000000013_S0000083	but i suppose where the area where which is most challenging is in my role as local government standards commissioner where i myself have been accused of sectarianism
POD1000000013_S0000084	because you know i was adjudicating on a a a particular councillor from a particular ah part of the unionist community
POD1000000013_S0000085	so there is that added layer of not only wanting to do things right to make the right decision but being aware that no matter what that decision is it might please one side or the other
POD1000000013_S0000086	so to be accused of sectarianism was a huge hurt for me because that's not that's not part of my values or my staff values
POD1000000013_S0000087	i mean that's a big issue because it affects you personally
POD1000000013_S0000088	how do you deal with that because you're a very resilient tough person but even that must be hard to deal with
POD1000000013_S0000089	well first of all i've got huge support from my deputy and the senior management team who reassured me that of course this isn't true and you know it isn't true and we know it isn't true
POD1000000013_S0000090	but i think what was difficult was the impact on my family and how they felt
POD1000000013_S0000091	my husband was angry and and my children were unhappy about it
POD1000000013_S0000092	and how did it affect me i learnt to deal with i learnt that you can deal with this sort of criticism
POD1000000013_S0000093	and i learnt that ah behind it all you've got to be sure that you're doing you're making the right decision
POD1000000013_S0000094	i can remember a few weeks ago when i was savagely criticised on twitter
POD1000000013_S0000095	and i was thirsting to reply and my oldest son said to me leave it alone dad they want you to reply
POD1000000013_S0000096	and i think that was quite wise advice
POD1000000013_S0000097	so you do need to consult with people on personal issues don't you
POD1000000013_S0000098	i think you do need to consult
POD1000000013_S0000099	and you do of what what's been helpful as been part of the ombudsman community's ah response to this is and you the personal support you've given me rob i was able to talk to you about it
POD1000000013_S0000100	i was able to talk to others like the current police ombudsman for northern ireland who've said leave it alone
POD1000000013_S0000101	just leave it because if you do anything if you take any legal action then it's merely going to provide more oxygen
POD1000000013_S0000102	yeah
POD1000000013_S0000103	doesn't stop it being difficult
POD1000000013_S0000104	no
POD1000000013_S0000105	personally difficult and that's where the resilience comes in
