POD1000000026_S0000258	both of us wanted to do something together again
POD1000000026_S0000259	like that was rare like most co-founder pairs find themselves in some sort of fight along the way and break up and
POD1000000026_S0000260	the idea that we could have a new challenge together potentially i think was what made it way more exciting
POD1000000026_S0000261	i'm not sure we were like looking for personal relationship when we started like a friendship
POD1000000026_S0000262	but the bond we have now is
POD1000000026_S0000264	i think i'd liken to people who like were in the military together
POD1000000026_S0000265	and i'm not like saying were we did anything even close to as important as that but when you go through things with someone when people try to kill your company when people try to throw you under the bus
POD1000000026_S0000266	all this stuff has happened to us and then some
POD1000000026_S0000267	and i remember very specifically this moment we ah we're having a disagreement with an investor
POD1000000026_S0000268	and we were so stressed out and we went to this really terrible taqueria on market street
POD1000000026_S0000269	but we sat down and we both ordered like the greasiest thing we could possibly imagine
POD1000000026_S0000270	and honestly that might have been a low in the company but it was a high for me
POD1000000026_S0000271	like i look back on that moment really fondly because it was us against the world
POD1000000026_S0000272	it was like we're gonna win this thing even if people don't believe in us even if we're having this thing go on like we're gonna make this work
POD1000000026_S0000273	call it friendship but that is like a bond that you don't form hanging out
POD1000000026_S0000274	the fact that we still like each other this long i think speaks to like a deeper trust and like real bond
POD1000000026_S0000275	but i think the fact that we liked each other after that first year which was like pure exposure spoke to trust but i think also just the
POD1000000026_S0000276	we have a way about each other that is not one that we find annoying
POD1000000026_S0000277	which sounds trivial but actually when if you're that around somebody for that long for that many days
POD1000000026_S0000278	you haven't showered in three days sometimes and you're eating the same lunch you've eaten every single day like
POD1000000026_S0000279	it's actually really important and hard to screen for in a like you know couple of nights in a coffee shop prototyping
POD1000000026_S0000280	i think that was a regard where we probably got lucky
POD1000000026_S0000281	couldn't have said it better that's exactly it
