YOU1000000003_S0000001	this is a three it's sloppily written and rendered at an extremely low resolution of twenty-eight by twenty-eight pixels
YOU1000000003_S0000002	but your brain has no trouble recognizing it as a three
YOU1000000003_S0000003	and i want you to take a moment to appreciate how crazy it is that brains can do this so effortlessly
YOU1000000003_S0000004	i mean this this and this are also recognizable as threes
YOU1000000003_S0000005	even though the specific values of each pixel is very different from one image to the next
YOU1000000003_S0000006	the particular light sensitive cells in your eye that are firing when you see this three are very different from the one's firing when you see this three
YOU1000000003_S0000007	but something in that crazy smart visual cortex of yours resolves these as representing the same idea
YOU1000000003_S0000008	while at the same time recognizing other images as their own distinct ideas
YOU1000000003_S0000009	but if i told you hey sit down and write for me a program that takes in a grid of twenty-eight by twenty-eight pixels like this
YOU1000000003_S0000010	and out put's a single number between zero and ten telling you what it thinks the digit is
