YOU1000000137_S0000290	but his success would never have been possible without a seemingly minor invention that revolutionized banking
YOU1000000137_S0000292	double-entry bookkeeping was the simple financial instrument that involved keeping a credit account showing income and a debit account with outgoing payments
YOU1000000137_S0000293	the first complete double-entry bookkeeping system can be traced back to thirteen forty in ledgers from genoa showing government income and expenditure
YOU1000000137_S0000295	double-entry bookkeeping showed account holders how much capital they had on hand allowing them greater overview and control of their finances
YOU1000000137_S0000297	the medicis were global players they issued loans and signed secure credit notes with travelers that could be cashed in many countries the precursor to today's travelers checks
